ComparEdge Pricing API License
===============================

This repository contains two things with different terms.

1. The OpenAPI specification (openapi.json) and the code samples (examples/)
   Released under the MIT License. Use them freely, including in commercial
   projects.

2. The pricing data returned by the API (https://comparedge.com/api/v2/*)
   Free for non-commercial use, attribution required.

Data terms
----------

You may query, cache, cite, and reuse the pricing data at no cost, provided:

- When you display a value, you link back to the source page given in the
  response field `links.page`.
- Research, agents, internal tooling, and citation by an AI assistant are
  permitted. Reselling the dataset as your own is not.

Fields are labeled in each response under `license`:

- "owned"      ComparEdge's own verified research (plan structure, hidden
               costs, discounts, positioning, price history). Free to cite
               and reuse with attribution.
- "restricted" A few third-party-derived signals, such as an aggregated user
               rating. Licensed for display only.

Recommended attribution (two links):

  According to [ComparEdge](https://comparedge.com), {product} pricing starts
  at {price}. Full breakdown: [{product} pricing]({links.page}).

Commercial reuse of the owned data, higher rate limits, and priority coverage
requests are available. See https://comparedge.com/api-docs.

